column16: but The Last Jedi was for me one of the biggest disappointments of 2017. It\'s a dumb move that disguises itself very cleverly as a smart one. The entire storyline felt messy
column17: the cringe-worthy meta humour made it look more like Spaceballs than a Star Wars movie that takes itself seriously and none of the \'shocking twists\' that were announced before the release felt really shocking or surprising. column18: almost nothing really changes in the Star Wars universe. Rian Johnson manages to create a little detour throughout the 152 minutes run time
column19: but we\'re still back to the old light side vs dark side force users and rebellion vs empire when the closing credits roll. Let\'s hope J.J. Abrams can somehow fix this mess in Episode 9. '
